# Spectrum 2 design system (strict)

When creating **new** components or **editing** existing ones under `src/`, UI must follow **Spectrum 2** via `@react-spectrum/s2`. This is non-negotiable for product UI.

## Required

- **Components**: Import primitives from `@react-spectrum/s2` (e.g. `Button`, `ActionButton`, `Text`, `Dialog`, `TextField`, `Provider`, …). Use the S2 component that matches the pattern instead of raw HTML controls (`<button>`, `<input>`, custom clickable `<div>`s) when S2 provides one.
- **Layout & visuals**: Use `style` (and `iconStyle` where needed) from `@react-spectrum/s2/style` with `with { type: 'macro' }`. Prefer Spectrum-oriented properties and tokens (`font:`, `color:`, spacing props, etc.) over ad-hoc pixel-perfect CSS that duplicates system semantics.
- **Icons**: Import from `@react-spectrum/s2/icons/<Name>` only.
- **App shell**: Root continues to use `Provider` from `@react-spectrum/s2` and global `@react-spectrum/s2/page.css` in the entry — do not replace with another design system or strip those.

## Forbidden for new or changed code

- **Do not** add or expand imports from `@adobe/react-spectrum` (Spectrum 1). If you touch a file that still uses it, **migrate that usage to `@react-spectrum/s2`** in the same change when feasible.
- **Do not** add alternate component libraries (e.g. shadcn, MUI, Chakra) for UI that belongs in Spectrum 2.
- **Do not** introduce Spectrum 1–specific packages or themes for new work.

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD — Spectrum 1 or raw control
import { Button } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';
<button type="button" onClick={...}>Save</button>

// GOOD — Spectrum 2
import { Button } from '@react-spectrum/s2';
import { style } from '@react-spectrum/s2/style' with { type: 'macro' };
```

If a needed control is missing from S2, prefer composing S2 primitives and `style()` before inventing a one-off widget; document the gap briefly in code comments only when necessary.
